<PageTitle>Badluck Achievements - Privacy policy</PageTitle>

<div class="section">
    <h2>1. Interpretation and Definitions</h2>
    <p>
        Key terms used in this policy have specific meanings:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Service</span>:
            Includes our website, Steam API integration, leaderboards, achievement quests,
            and all related gaming features/platform functionality.
        </li>

        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Steam Data</span>:
            Publicly available information from your Steam profile including but not limited to:
            game achievements, playtime statistics, friend lists, and public profile details.
        </li>

        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Account Data</span>:
            Information you provide during registration and use, including email address,
            username, preferences, and connected third-party accounts.
        </li>

        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Cookies</span>:
            Small text files stored on your device that enable features like persistent logins,
            preference memory, and analytics tracking. Manage them via browser settings.
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>2. Data Collection</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Steam-Specific Data</span> (via Steam API):
            <ul>
                <li>Steam username, profile URL, avatar, game achievements, playtime, and public friend lists</li>
                <li>Data used for leaderboards, quest tracking, and personalized recommendations</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><span class="highlight">Account Data</span>: Email, username, password (hashed), and preferences</li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Usage Data</span>:
            <ul>
                <li>IP address, browser type, device identifiers, pages visited, session duration</li>
                <li>Interactions with leaderboards, quests, and achievement analytics</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <span class="highlight">Cookies</span>:
            <ul>
                <li><span class="highlight">Essential</span>: Session cookies for login (expire after 24 hours)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Functional</span>: Language/theme preferences (expire after 30 days)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Analytics</span>: Google Analytics (_ga, _gid) to track feature usage (expire after 2 years)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>

